common.filter.object.description: Filter the result according to a set of criteria.

common.range.object.description: Limit the number of output. For a range of [a, n], the output will contain n elements, starting from the ath matching result.

common.sort.object.description: Specify the sorting of the returned result.

params.cdb.get.obj.option.opts.description:
Set fetch option for the request. If no option is specified, by default the attributes of the object will be returned.
object member - Return a list of object members along with other attributes.
chksum - Return the check-sum value instead of attributes.

params.cdb.get.table.option.opts.description:
Set fetch option for the request. If no option is specified, by default the attributes of the objects will be returned.
count - Return the number of matching entries instead of the actual entry data.
object member - Return a list of object members along with other attributes.
datasrc - Return all objects that can be referenced by an attribute. Require attr parameter.
get reserved - Also return reserved objects in the result.
syntax - Return the attribute syntax of a table or an object, instead of the actual entry data. All filter parameters will be ignored.

action.description: Action to take for this content type.

category.description: Categories that this content type applies to.

action.description: Block or exempt word when a match is found.

pattern-type.description: Banned word pattern type: wildcard pattern or Perl regular expression.

score.description: Score, to be applied every time the word appears on a web page (0 - 4294967295, default = 10).

extended-log.description: Enable/disable extended logging for web filtering.

post-action.description: Action taken for HTTP POST traffic.

web-content-log.description: Enable/disable logging logging blocked web content.

web-extended-all-action-log.description: Enable/disable extended any filter action logging for web filtering.

check-basic-auth.description: Enable/disable checking of HTTP Basic Auth field for known credentials.

check-uri.description: Enable/disable checking of GET URI parameters for known credentials.

check-username-only.description: Enable/disable acting only on valid username credentials. Action will be taken for valid usernames regardless of password validity.

default-action.description: Action to be taken when there is no matching rule.

domain-controller.description: Domain for which to verify received credentials against.

max-body-len.description: Maximum size of a POST body to check for credentials.

action.description: Action to be taken upon an AntiPhishing match.

exempt-quota.description: Do not stop quota for these categories.

max-quota-timeout.description: Maximum FortiGuard quota used by single page view in seconds (excludes streams).

category.description: Categories and groups the filter examines.

warning-duration-type.description: Re-display warning after closing browser or after a timeout.

warning-prompt.description: Warning prompts in each category or each domain.

category.description: FortiGuard categories to apply quota to (category action must be set to monitor).

ovrd-user-group.description: User groups with permission to use the override.

profile.description: Web filter profile with permission to create overrides.

profile-attribute.description: Profile attribute to retrieve from the RADIUS server.

redirect-header.description: HTTP header name to use for client redirect on blocked requests

redirect-no-content.description: Enable / Disable empty message-body entity in HTTP response

redirect-url.description: HTTP header value to use for client redirect on blocked requests

server-fqdn.description: URL extraction server FQDN (fully qualified domain name)

blacklist.description: Enable/disable automatic addition of URLs detected by FortiSandbox to blacklist.

keyword-match.description: Search keywords to log when match is found.

channel-id.description: YouTube channel ID to be filtered.

ip-addr-block.description: Enable/disable blocking URLs when the hostname appears as an IP address.

one-arm-ips-urlfilter.description: Enable/disable DNS resolver for one-arm IPS URL filter operation.

action.description: Action to take for URL filter matches.

antiphish-action.description: Action to take for AntiPhishing matches.

dns-address-family.description: Resolve IPv4 address, IPv6 address, or both from DNS server.

exempt.description: If action is set to exempt, select the security profile operations that exempt URLs skip. Separate multiple options with a space.
